        <h2>Animals at the centre, <em>always</em></h2>
        <p class="prose">Alpacas and llamas offer unique qualities for the relationship with people: a calm temperament, an accessible size and a gentle appearance. Our work puts the animal's welfare at the centre of every intervention.</p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li><div><strong>Assisted activities (AAI):</strong> educational and socialisation programmes in school, community and social-care settings.</div></li>
          <li><div><strong>Research and protocols:</strong> study of behavioural and physiological parameters of welfare and stress during activities, to define validated protocols.</div></li>
          <li><div><strong>Training and supervision:</strong> support in designing interventions that respect the ethological needs of the species.</div></li>
